01:49.759 --> 01:50.760
(HORSE SNORTING)

02:02.159 --> 02:04.685
NAPOLEON: At last, Moscow.

02:05.959 --> 02:08.439
Here she lies in all her beauty.

02:08.519 --> 02:09.520
Wide open to us.

02:11.839 --> 02:15.082
With one word from me,
she could be destroyed forever.

02:16.519 --> 02:17.725
But I will spare her,

02:18.199 --> 02:19.200
and more than that,

02:20.239 --> 02:21.843
I will bring her justice

02:23.199 --> 02:25.725
and show her the meaning of true civilisation.

02:26.759 --> 02:29.524
I will be merciful
with her former rulers.

02:29.599 --> 02:32.489
I will say to them, "I come in peace."

02:33.279 --> 02:38.604
"Your happiness is as precious to me
as that of all my subjects."

02:40.479 --> 02:42.686
This is the dawn of a
new age in Russia.

02:43.519 --> 02:45.089
- (MEN SCREAMING)
- (GLASS SHATTERING)

02:47.559 --> 02:49.482
(IN DISTINCT CHATTERING)

02:49.599 --> 02:51.442
MAN: (SHOUTING)
Thieves! Stop.

02:51.519 --> 02:52.680
That's mine!

02:52.759 --> 02:53.760
(GRUNTING)

02:54.079 --> 02:55.160
(GROANING)

02:58.679 --> 03:01.046
(IN DISTINCT CHATTERING)

03:05.719 --> 03:07.881
(IN DISTINCT CHATTERING)

03:15.039 --> 03:16.849
(GEESE CACKLING)

03:19.719 --> 03:21.084
WOMAN: Put all the silver
in that one.

03:21.159 --> 03:22.239
PETYA: Everyone is leaving.

03:22.319 --> 03:24.399
They're looting the shops
and fighting in the street.

03:24.759 --> 03:26.727
- We have to leave now.
- Now, let's not get ahead of ourselves.

03:26.799 --> 03:27.800
There is plenty of time.

03:27.879 --> 03:30.962
There's all sorts of rumours flying
around, but the Governor can't risk...

03:31.039 --> 03:32.370
People are saying he's left as well.

03:32.439 --> 03:33.645
What's happening?

03:33.719 --> 03:35.084
Papa, we have to leave.

03:35.279 --> 03:37.088
Why do we always leave everything
till it's too late?

03:37.199 --> 03:39.406
Don't you understand?
The French are coming now.

03:39.479 --> 03:41.243
Oh, what is to become of us?

03:41.919 --> 03:43.683
ILYA: It's all going to be fine, darling.

03:43.919 --> 03:45.842
Can I help?
What do you want me to do?

03:45.919 --> 03:47.444
NATALYA: No, no, don't touch that.

03:58.479 --> 03:59.519
MAN: Redress those wounds.

03:59.559 --> 04:00.560
- Particularly your...
- Excuse me.

04:00.879 --> 04:02.563
Sorry, where have you come from?

04:02.639 --> 04:04.482
- Borodino.
- Is there any way we can help?

04:04.559 --> 04:06.243
Well, food and water,
if you have any.

04:06.919 --> 04:07.920
Of course. Errn...

04:09.079 --> 04:10.922
The wounded, who can't walk,

04:11.399 --> 04:12.844
wouldn't it better
if they were brought in?

04:12.919 --> 04:14.921
We have plenty of room.
Would it be permitted?

04:14.999 --> 04:16.000
You're very kind.

04:16.079 --> 04:18.366
Forgive me, Your Excellency,
are you permitted?

04:18.559 --> 04:19.798
Should you not ask your father?

04:19.879 --> 04:21.721
It's all right, he'll say yes.
I know he will.

04:21.879 --> 04:22.880
Have them brought in.

04:23.119 --> 04:24.120
Thank you.

04:24.519 --> 04:26.283
Onward, bring the horses inside.

04:26.799 --> 04:28.722
Bring the wounded inside.

04:30.559 --> 04:32.448
I don't know what to take
and what to leave.

04:32.919 --> 04:34.523
You should pack
for Nikolai, too.

04:35.119 --> 04:36.679
I wish he was here
to say what he needs.

04:36.759 --> 04:39.080
Oh, I think he has
what he needs already.

04:40.919 --> 04:42.205
Sonya, you know he loves you.

04:42.479 --> 04:44.129
Yes, but what does that matter?

04:46.159 --> 04:48.161
I can't imagine Nikolai
loving anybody else.

04:48.239 --> 04:49.286
Mmm.

04:49.359 --> 04:51.930
Anyway, if anyone's going
to be an old maid, it will be me.

04:53.119 --> 04:55.201
No one will want me after my disgrace.

04:57.919 --> 04:59.603
You're still my friend, though,
aren't you, Sonya?

04:59.679 --> 05:02.444
I know I said some awful things to you
at that terrible time.

05:02.999 --> 05:05.650
Yes, of course I'm still your friend.

05:06.639 --> 05:08.687
(SIGHS) Then I am happy.

05:09.839 --> 05:11.204
You and Pierre, that's enough.

05:13.079 --> 05:14.604
I do wonder what happened to Pierre.

05:16.719 --> 05:18.319
Do you think we will ever see him again?

05:18.879 --> 05:20.768
Oh, I can't imagine not.

05:21.799 --> 05:22.800
No.

05:23.479 --> 05:24.480
How could I?

05:28.599 --> 05:29.760
Oh, Sonya...

05:31.159 --> 05:33.207
What's going to happen
to those poor, wounded soldiers

05:33.279 --> 05:34.690
when the French get here?

05:35.679 --> 05:37.249
The French are not barbarians.

05:38.439 --> 05:40.601
Well, perhaps we could take
one or two of them with us.

05:40.679 --> 05:43.444
We can make space.
I'm... I'm going to ask Papa.

05:45.199 --> 05:46.439
I won't allow it!

05:46.839 --> 05:47.840
Ream, “Ilya.

05:48.039 --> 05:49.245
You have brought us to the point where

05:49.319 --> 05:50.879
we're not getting
anything for our house

05:50.919 --> 05:53.286
and now you want us to give up
all our possessions?

05:53.359 --> 05:54.849
All our children's inheritance?

05:54.919 --> 05:58.640
But if we can care two or three
of these poor fellows, Natalya...

05:58.719 --> 06:00.084
It isn't our business to care for them.

06:00.159 --> 06:02.039
It's the government's business
to care for them.

06:02.079 --> 06:03.319
The government's gone, my dear.

06:03.399 --> 06:06.721
Oh, so you want to us to abandon
all our family treasures to the French

06:06.879 --> 06:09.086
just to make room in the carriages
for soldiers? No.

06:09.559 --> 06:13.450
No! This is beyond your usual
foolishness, this is, this is madness!

06:13.519 --> 06:15.442
Mama, please.
It's not abandoning everything,

06:15.519 --> 06:17.328
it's just things
we wouldn't care about...

06:17.399 --> 06:19.049
These are our things!

06:19.919 --> 06:21.762
Aren't you ashamed of yourself?

06:22.239 --> 06:23.240
(SCOFFS)

06:24.159 --> 06:25.160
Do what you will.

06:25.879 --> 06:26.880
Ruin us!

06:27.119 --> 06:28.120
I give UP-.

06:28.199 --> 06:29.246
(SOBBING)

06:33.479 --> 06:34.765
(BELLS RINGING SOFTLY)

06:57.719 --> 06:59.244
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

06:59.999 --> 07:01.000
(KNOCK ON DOOR)

07:09.759 --> 07:11.045
(IN DISTINCT CHATTER)

07:20.839 --> 07:22.648
Take a last look at the old house.

07:23.039 --> 07:24.399
Who knows when we'll return to it.

07:24.479 --> 07:25.969
NATALYA: Never, no doubt.

07:26.519 --> 07:27.938
ILYA: Ah, I am not so sure.

07:28.519 --> 07:31.329
Things have a way of turning out for
the bestjust when you least expect it.

07:31.399 --> 07:35.199
Ugh, your blind optimism
never ceases to amaze me.

07:48.839 --> 07:49.965
Extraordinary.

07:50.719 --> 07:51.766
NATALYA: It's appalling.

07:51.959 --> 07:53.006
I can't look.

07:55.119 --> 07:57.087
(IN DISTINCT CHATTERING)

07:57.999 --> 07:59.000
Wait.

07:59.319 --> 08:01.208
Wait, stop, isn't that Pierre?

08:01.279 --> 08:02.929
Please stop the carriage!

08:03.279 --> 08:04.440
CARRIAGE DRIVER:
Miss, we can't stop here.

08:04.639 --> 08:05.640
Pierre!

08:06.039 --> 08:07.086
Pierre!

08:09.799 --> 08:12.484
What are you doing?
Why are you dressed like that?

08:15.479 --> 08:16.480
You don't look yourself.

08:17.519 --> 08:19.123
Come with us.
You can't stay in Moscow.

08:19.199 --> 08:20.644
Yes, I'm afraid I have to.

08:20.719 --> 08:21.720
Why?

08:21.799 --> 08:24.530
There's something I have to do,
something terrible.

08:25.279 --> 08:26.280
What?

08:27.519 --> 08:28.759
Kill Napoleon.

08:31.079 --> 08:32.080
Pierre!

08:34.479 --> 08:35.525
Pierre!

08:38.879 --> 08:40.005
Pierre!

08:43.719 --> 08:44.720
What's the hurry?

08:45.119 --> 08:46.120
The French are here.

08:46.279 --> 08:47.485
They are in the city.

09:13.439 --> 09:18.764
(MAN SINGING IN FRENCH)

09:25.599 --> 09:28.603
(SINGING CONTINUES)

09:35.479 --> 09:36.480
Who the hell are you?

09:38.839 --> 09:40.682
Who the hell are you, monsieur?

09:41.519 --> 09:44.762
I am Count Pierre Bezukhov.
I own this house.

09:46.199 --> 09:47.200
Ah.

09:49.839 --> 09:52.001
Capitaine Rambal,
4e régiment de chasseurs.

09:52.079 --> 09:53.729
A votre service, Monsieur Le Comte.

09:54.519 --> 09:56.726
I must inform you that your
house has been commandeered

09:56.799 --> 09:58.130
in the name of the French Army.

09:58.239 --> 09:59.240
Has it, by God?

10:02.399 --> 10:04.049
We are both gentlemen, monsieur.

10:04.759 --> 10:07.285
I'm weary of war.

10:08.119 --> 10:10.520
And hungry for a little
civilised conversation.

10:12.039 --> 10:13.325
Come, sit.

10:14.319 --> 10:15.844
And drink a bottle or two with me.

10:20.119 --> 10:21.501
(SOFTLY) Oh, what the hell.

10:23.439 --> 10:24.804
Capitaine Rambal.

10:25.479 --> 10:27.686
Is Napoleon himself in the city here?

10:27.799 --> 10:28.800
Certainement.

10:28.879 --> 10:30.768
He will be addressing the
populace tomorrow evening

10:30.839 --> 10:32.967
from the steps of the Kremlin Palace.

10:33.039 --> 10:34.040
He's there now.

10:34.839 --> 10:35.840
Tell me, Count,

10:36.279 --> 10:38.202
have all the women left Moscow?

10:38.319 --> 10:39.400
- I believe so.
- Ah...

10:40.199 --> 10:41.564
All those who had the means to.

10:41.839 --> 10:42.840
Dommage.

10:42.919 --> 10:44.125
(LAUGHS)

10:44.199 --> 10:45.200
I love women.

10:45.359 --> 10:47.327
Women have been my life.

10:47.559 --> 10:50.290
And I can tell
you have known women, too.

10:50.399 --> 10:51.400
Eh?

10:52.479 --> 10:53.480
Just a month ago,

10:54.119 --> 10:57.202
I had the honour to save the
life of a Polish Hussar.

10:57.759 --> 10:58.760
And you know what?

10:59.679 --> 11:02.000
He insisted on offering his wife to me.

11:02.399 --> 11:06.040
(LAUGHS) A very affectionate
little thing she was.

11:07.199 --> 11:09.008
She wanted to run away with me,
you know?

11:09.799 --> 11:13.008
But when I'd had my fill,
I returned her to her husband.

11:13.239 --> 11:14.570
"Monsieur, " I said to him.

11:14.639 --> 11:18.689
"I saved your life, and now
I will save your honour."

11:18.879 --> 11:20.563
(LAUGHS)

11:20.639 --> 11:22.687
I must confess, I am a romantic.

11:23.399 --> 11:26.687
And I can tell you are
the same, my friend.

11:27.079 --> 11:28.080
(SOFFLY) No.

11:28.439 --> 11:30.248
No, not quite the same.

11:32.039 --> 11:35.885
I have a different view of love from
yours and a different experience of it.

11:36.719 --> 11:39.882
Of course, I've known women,
many of them, I'm ashamed to say.

11:42.559 --> 11:46.609
But I have only truly loved
one woman in all my life.

11:49.639 --> 11:50.640
Hmm.

11:50.839 --> 11:52.284
And she can never belong to me.

12:05.359 --> 12:06.360
(GROANS)

12:06.839 --> 12:08.364
What's this place called?

12:08.559 --> 12:10.129
Mytishchi, I think they said.

12:11.039 --> 12:12.404
ILYA: Oh, Mytishchi, yes.

12:12.839 --> 12:14.409
I hope we get further, though.

12:14.719 --> 12:16.084
Started out so late.

12:16.279 --> 12:17.521
NATASHA: Sonya, come with me.

12:23.799 --> 12:24.800
Careful.

12:25.319 --> 12:27.048
Please let me help you.

12:28.079 --> 12:30.712
(IN DISTINCT CHATTERING)

12:30.839 --> 12:32.045
May I help here?

12:32.519 --> 12:33.964
Is he very badly wounded?

12:34.079 --> 12:36.446
Yes, he should have a room to himself.

12:36.519 --> 12:38.009
If that's possible, miss.

12:38.439 --> 12:40.282
- He is quite an important person.
- Well.

12:43.879 --> 12:44.880
Oh.

12:46.719 --> 12:49.290
Yes, I'll... I'll tell the mistress
right away.

12:49.519 --> 12:51.044
He'll have every care possible.

12:56.999 --> 12:58.330
Look there, Your Excellency.

12:58.879 --> 12:59.880
Back there.

13:00.559 --> 13:01.560
That's fire.

13:02.719 --> 13:04.337
Moscow is burning.

13:06.079 --> 13:07.864
(GASPS)

13:10.439 --> 13:11.440
Oh, Moscow.

13:12.159 --> 13:15.208
Never mind, Excellency.
They will put it out.

13:15.559 --> 13:16.560
No fear.

13:18.239 --> 13:20.207
But who is left to put it out?

13:20.279 --> 13:21.690
(SOFTLY) Poor Moscow.

13:24.199 --> 13:25.532
Our dear mother.

13:41.679 --> 13:42.680
(SNORING)

13:48.439 --> 13:49.804
(SNORING)

14:36.279 --> 14:39.886
(WOMAN SCREAMING)

14:43.959 --> 14:45.768
Help me, for the love of God,
my little girl.

14:45.839 --> 14:48.445
My youngest, she got left behind.
She'll be all burnt up.

14:48.519 --> 14:50.283
- Where did you leave her?
- She's in there, God help her.

14:50.359 --> 14:52.680
(SHOUTING IN FRENCH)

14:53.439 --> 14:54.440
Come with me!

14:54.719 --> 14:56.369
You can get in round the side, please.

14:57.479 --> 14:58.605
Hurry, hurry...

14:58.679 --> 14:59.680
Wait here.

15:10.039 --> 15:12.440
(SHOUTING)
Help! A little girl, have you seen her?

15:12.879 --> 15:13.880
(CRASHING)

15:15.839 --> 15:17.728
(CHILD CRYING)

15:18.999 --> 15:20.728
(CHILD'S CRY GETS LOUDER)

15:20.799 --> 15:21.800
Oh, good.

15:22.359 --> 15:23.360
It's all right.

15:23.639 --> 15:24.686
It's okay, I've got you.

15:25.319 --> 15:27.367
- (CHILD CRYING)
- Hey, it's all right.

15:30.559 --> 15:31.560
It's all right.

15:38.679 --> 15:39.726
Where's your mother gone?

15:39.799 --> 15:41.759
The soldiers moved them on.
They're that way, sir.

15:41.799 --> 15:42.880
(WOMAN SCREAMING)

15:43.159 --> 15:44.320
(SHOUTS IN FRENCH)

15:44.839 --> 15:47.206
Here. Leave her alone!

15:47.279 --> 15:48.440
(EXCLAIMING)

15:51.199 --> 15:52.724
(EXCLAIMING)

15:59.999 --> 16:01.603
(SCREAMING)

16:01.879 --> 16:04.041
(CROWD SHOUTING)

16:05.039 --> 16:07.360
PIERRE: Come on, then!
I'll fight you all!

16:09.959 --> 16:10.960
No!

16:12.239 --> 16:13.240
Assassin.

16:13.639 --> 16:15.084
Assassin et pyromane.

16:16.119 --> 16:17.928
(SCREAMING) No!

16:18.079 --> 16:20.002
(SCREAMING)

16:25.719 --> 16:28.040
I think all of Moscow will burn down,
Sonya.

16:28.239 --> 16:29.843
It's such a terrible glow.

16:33.519 --> 16:34.520
(MAN COUGHING)

16:37.999 --> 16:39.000
(SOFTLY) Natasha.

16:40.319 --> 16:44.040
Your mother told me not say anything,
but I think you should know.

16:46.159 --> 16:47.160
Know what?

16:49.919 --> 16:50.920
Prince Andrei is here.

16:53.679 --> 16:54.680
In this...

16:55.479 --> 16:56.480
In this house?

16:56.839 --> 16:59.046
He is in the back room.
He is very badly wounded.

16:59.119 --> 17:01.326
Too badly to see anyone, they said.

17:03.559 --> 17:06.130
(MAN COUGHING)

17:06.279 --> 17:08.566
- Is that him?
- No, no. That's the other one.

17:08.638 --> 17:10.403
He lies very quiet.

17:10.959 --> 17:12.199
(MAN COUGHING)

17:12.398 --> 17:13.400
NATALYA: Tasha?

17:14.079 --> 17:15.358
You'll catch a chill over there.

17:16.079 --> 17:17.319
Come and lie in bed with me.

17:17.559 --> 17:19.367
No, I'm all right, Mama.

17:19.999 --> 17:21.728
I'll sleep over here on the ﬂoor.

17:53.639 --> 17:54.640
(SNORING)

18:10.119 --> 18:11.120
(SNIFFLING)

18:16.319 --> 18:17.320
(noon BANGS)

18:17.879 --> 18:19.369
Hey, miss, you can't be here.

18:19.439 --> 18:20.440
No, let her stay.

18:23.359 --> 18:25.009
It's really you.

18:26.999 --> 18:28.569
(KISSING HAND)

18:28.639 --> 18:29.800
Forgive me.

18:29.879 --> 18:31.688
(SOBBING)
I'm so sorry, forgive me.

18:32.359 --> 18:33.360
For what?

18:33.599 --> 18:34.760
For what I did.

18:35.079 --> 18:36.080
ANDREI: Natasha.

18:37.479 --> 18:38.480
I love you.

18:39.599 --> 18:41.109
NATASHA: (SOFTLY)
You can't love me.

18:43.519 --> 18:44.884
I love you more.

18:46.999 --> 18:48.410
Better than I did before.

18:50.039 --> 18:51.348
I was in the wrong.

18:52.279 --> 18:54.680
It's for you to forgive me.

19:01.839 --> 19:04.649
(PEOPLE CHATTERING)

19:12.919 --> 19:14.444
- Hi.
- I had thought you left.

19:14.679 --> 19:16.751
Came to tell you that I've heard
your brother is alive.

19:16.799 --> 19:19.962
He's being cared for by my family.
They'll be travelling to Yaroslavl.

19:20.479 --> 19:21.810
They had to flee from Moscow.

19:21.919 --> 19:23.842
Thank God.

19:24.799 --> 19:27.279
I must bring Nikolushka
to see his father.

19:27.359 --> 19:28.360
NIKOLAI: Yes, of course.

19:29.719 --> 19:31.926
I would escort you, but I am already
late to join my regiment.

19:31.999 --> 19:34.127
No, no, don't be silly.

19:37.519 --> 19:39.760
Nothing ever happens exactly as
one would wish, but...

19:40.079 --> 19:41.080
I understand.

19:43.839 --> 19:44.886
Bye, Nikolai.

19:45.519 --> 19:46.520
Stay safe.

19:51.639 --> 19:52.640
Say bye.

19:58.839 --> 19:59.840
Where's Natasha?

20:00.839 --> 20:02.284
She's still not with that man?

20:02.399 --> 20:03.400
She won't leave his side.

20:03.479 --> 20:06.847
Well, tell her to come and make ready,
we have to move on.

20:06.999 --> 20:09.730
She says that Prince Andrei
isn't well enough to be moved yet.

20:09.919 --> 20:10.920
(SIGHS)

20:11.039 --> 20:13.690
Ilya, what are we to do?
Should we move on?

20:13.959 --> 20:16.246
Or is it safe to wait a day or two?

20:17.039 --> 20:18.040
Er...

20:19.479 --> 20:20.526
Hard to say, er...

20:22.159 --> 20:23.359
I'll leave it to you, my dear.

20:24.039 --> 20:26.129
I'm just going to step out
for a breath of fresh air.

20:26.799 --> 20:27.846
See the goats, you know.

20:30.519 --> 20:31.520
NATALYA: Oh, my God.

20:32.199 --> 20:33.564
What are we going to do?

20:35.359 --> 20:36.360
This has...

20:37.559 --> 20:38.560
Broken him.

20:42.559 --> 20:45.039
You know we are ruined, don't you?

20:46.719 --> 20:48.323
We have nothing left.

20:49.599 --> 20:50.600
Nothing at all.

20:52.559 --> 20:55.369
Everything now depends on Nikolai.

20:55.559 --> 20:56.560
(SNIFFLES)

20:58.479 --> 21:00.131
Everything.

21:02.479 --> 21:04.096
You understand me?

21:05.239 --> 21:06.968
Yes, Countess, I understand you.

21:17.319 --> 21:18.320
(SIGHS)

21:22.799 --> 21:24.688
(GOATS BLEATING)

21:41.999 --> 21:44.650
(MILITARY DRUM PLAYING)

21:47.759 --> 21:50.888
(MEN SPEAKING FRENCH)

21:54.439 --> 21:56.248
(GROANING)

21:57.959 --> 21:59.165
(STRUGGLING)

22:02.079 --> 22:03.358
(MAN GROANING)

22:08.119 --> 22:10.633
(MAN MUMBLING SOFTLY)

22:17.839 --> 22:19.268
FRENCH SOLDIER: Présentez armes!

22:21.519 --> 22:22.520
En joue!

22:24.719 --> 22:26.608
- Feu!
- (GUNS FIRING)

22:26.719 --> 22:28.032
Les deux suivants. Vite.

22:28.079 --> 22:29.126
(MAN SCREAMING)

22:29.959 --> 22:31.802
(MAN SCREAMING)

22:32.039 --> 22:33.040
(MAN SCREAMING)

22:34.119 --> 22:36.087
(MAN GROANING IN PAIN)

22:40.519 --> 22:41.520
En joue.

22:41.599 --> 22:43.203
(GUNS COCKING)

22:43.599 --> 22:45.920
- Feu!
- (GUNS FIRING)

22:57.399 --> 22:59.242
Non, non, non.
(SPEAKING FRENCH)

22:59.999 --> 23:02.189
- Les autres sont la' comme temo.
- (MAN SCREAMING)

23:02.519 --> 23:04.123
(MAN SCREAMING)

23:05.719 --> 23:07.642
(MAN SCREAMING)

23:09.399 --> 23:11.359
- (SOLDIER SPEAKING FRENCH)
- (MAN SCREAMING)

23:13.039 --> 23:14.040
(MAN SCREAMING)

23:14.559 --> 23:15.560
En joue.

23:17.719 --> 23:20.484
- Feu!
- (GUNS FIRING)

23:21.239 --> 23:22.889
(SOLIDER SPEAKING FRENCH)

23:26.119 --> 23:27.803
ANDREY. Everything is simple, really.

23:28.759 --> 23:29.760
The world...

23:31.199 --> 23:32.564
The world wants us to love it.

23:33.079 --> 23:35.366
And it's not hard, it's easy.

23:36.679 --> 23:38.886
I heard this little whispering voice,

23:39.959 --> 23:41.802
sort of little whispering music.

23:42.879 --> 23:44.881
I realised it was a fly in the room.

23:45.839 --> 23:47.887
And it wanted me to love it.

23:48.919 --> 23:50.330
And I did love it.

23:51.879 --> 23:54.883
And I saw that one can love everything.

23:57.159 --> 23:59.159
(SOFFLY) Don't talk too much,
you'll tire yourself.

23:59.199 --> 24:00.200
Am I talking nonsense?

24:01.479 --> 24:03.039
I've been delirious, you know.

24:04.639 --> 24:05.896
But I want...

24:06.319 --> 24:08.048
I want you to know that I...

24:09.359 --> 24:10.759
(SIGHS)

24:10.881 --> 24:12.217
I'm happy...

24:15.559 --> 24:17.231
I saw him

24:17.363 --> 24:18.385
at the hospital.

24:18.405 --> 24:19.719
Who, who did you see?

24:20.119 --> 24:21.280
Anatole Kuragin.

24:22.559 --> 24:23.560
My anew'!

24:24.959 --> 24:26.370
He was hurt

24:27.359 --> 24:29.600
and I was hurt, and he looked at me,

24:30.479 --> 24:32.720
and I found that I loved him, too.

24:34.599 --> 24:35.600
He's not so bad.

24:37.039 --> 24:39.121
He can't help it, being like that.

24:40.159 --> 24:42.241
And I'm the one to blame.

24:43.799 --> 24:46.086
It was cruel of me to leave you.

24:46.439 --> 24:48.009
It was cruel of me
to break it off with you.

24:48.159 --> 24:50.605
- I see that now.
- No, please, don't talk like that.

24:50.719 --> 24:51.720
As if I were a child.

24:52.679 --> 24:54.886
As if I have no responsibility
for what I did.

24:55.479 --> 24:56.480
I was wrong.

24:57.159 --> 24:58.160
And I was foolish.

24:58.359 --> 25:00.805
And I didn't think of you
or how I was hurting you.

25:01.399 --> 25:02.639
I behaved badly.

25:03.719 --> 25:06.404
And nothing can change that.
Nothing can make it right.

25:07.959 --> 25:09.882
But we can forgive each other,
can't we?

25:10.679 --> 25:12.169
We can still love each other.

25:13.039 --> 25:14.643
Now that it's all too late.

25:15.159 --> 25:17.321
But it isn't.
It isn't too late.

25:19.599 --> 25:20.600
It's so strange.

25:22.319 --> 25:23.320
I was thinking,

25:24.559 --> 25:25.560
"If she could be here,

25:26.439 --> 25:27.440
"I could tell her."

25:28.079 --> 25:29.080
And here you are.

25:29.799 --> 25:30.925
And I won't leave you.

25:31.439 --> 25:33.043
I'll never leave you.

25:54.799 --> 25:55.800
NIKOLAY. "My dear Sonya."

25:56.759 --> 25:58.974
- Ugh...
- (FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

26:01.439 --> 26:02.479
Did I ask you to barge in?

26:02.639 --> 26:04.403
Sorry, Your Excellency,

26:04.639 --> 26:06.289
but this letter...

26:06.559 --> 26:07.560
All right, give it here.

26:13.279 --> 26:14.963
SONYA". My dearest Nikolai,

26:15.519 --> 26:18.921
I am writing to tell you that
I release you from our engagement.

26:18.999 --> 26:20.683
Oh, thank you, God.

26:21.119 --> 26:22.120
(SIGHS)

26:23.919 --> 26:27.560
SONYA". I know that your family wish
you to marry Princess Bolkonskaya,

26:28.079 --> 26:30.559
that your family's welfare
depends upon it.

26:31.239 --> 26:33.606
So I beg you to consider yourself free.

26:34.119 --> 26:36.008
But to know that despite everything,

26:36.719 --> 26:39.040
no one could love you more than...

26:41.679 --> 26:43.489
Your Sonya.

26:45.879 --> 26:46.926
NATALYA: Sonya!

26:47.839 --> 26:48.840
Sonya!

26:49.279 --> 26:50.724
Sonya, we have to leave!

26:58.759 --> 27:00.602
BENNIGSEN: I say now is the
time to attack Napoleon.

27:00.679 --> 27:02.408
While his divisions
are scattered across the city

27:02.479 --> 27:05.369
and his soldiers are preoccupied
with arresting looters.

27:05.719 --> 27:07.369
Those who are not looting themselves.

27:07.639 --> 27:10.643
We could retake Moscow
and secure a famous victory.

27:10.719 --> 27:11.969
No.

27:12.639 --> 27:13.640
We do nothing.

27:14.279 --> 27:15.565
Time and patience.

27:15.879 --> 27:18.405
Napoleon will never survive
the Russian winter.

27:18.959 --> 27:21.041
In a little while,
he will abandon Moscow

27:21.119 --> 27:23.850
because he has no means
of supplying his army.

27:24.359 --> 27:26.282
Then, when he is retreating,

27:26.599 --> 27:27.600
we will attack.

27:27.759 --> 27:30.490
Consider the advantage of fighting
on our own ground.

27:30.559 --> 27:32.368
(PEOPLE ARGUING)

27:32.439 --> 27:34.407
Meeting concluded, gentlemen.

27:37.799 --> 27:39.079
NAPOLEON: This is beyond reason.

27:40.559 --> 27:41.560
They refuse to fight,

27:42.319 --> 27:44.584
yet they don't surrender
and make terms.

27:46.199 --> 27:47.638
What sort of men are they?

27:47.999 --> 27:49.728
That they would burn
their beloved city to the ground

27:49.799 --> 27:51.881
rather than accept
my generous settlement.

27:53.799 --> 27:54.846
Are they savages?

27:56.719 --> 27:58.562
Do they want to go back
to the Dark Ages?

27:59.919 --> 28:01.205
I expected better of them.

28:03.479 --> 28:04.890
I am disappointed!

28:11.679 --> 28:12.680
(CLEARING TH ROAT)

28:12.759 --> 28:14.648
- Sire.
- Yes, what?

28:18.159 --> 28:20.048
What with the disruptions and the fires,

28:20.119 --> 28:23.089
we shall soon find we are running
out of essential provisions.

28:23.599 --> 28:24.879
And you think I don't know that?

28:27.199 --> 28:28.689
I shall be glad to receive
your solutions

28:28.759 --> 28:30.409
to these problems by noon today.

28:45.279 --> 28:47.805
(MEN SCREAMING)

28:48.039 --> 28:49.040
(SUM FIRING)

28:49.399 --> 28:50.810
- (SWORD SWISHING)
- (MAN SCREAMING)

28:50.999 --> 28:53.650
- (GUN COCKING)
- (GUN FIRING)

28:59.799 --> 29:01.528
(BREATHS DEEPLY)

29:05.839 --> 29:07.193
(MAN COUGHING)

29:20.319 --> 29:21.758
MAN: You all right, master?

29:23.439 --> 29:25.282
There are no masters here, I think.

29:26.719 --> 29:28.448
I think you're right there.

29:31.039 --> 29:32.689
What, you've seen a bit of trouble?

29:33.199 --> 29:34.200
I have.

29:35.559 --> 29:36.560
Dare say you have, too.

29:37.079 --> 29:38.319
Ah, we won't dwell on that.

29:39.039 --> 29:41.690
You suffer now, you'll have a lifetime,
it all comes around.

29:43.959 --> 29:45.165
Don't have any worries here.

29:45.879 --> 29:47.369
It's up to them lot to look after us.

29:48.639 --> 29:49.640
(DOG WHINING)

29:51.719 --> 29:52.720
Wait a minute.

29:54.399 --> 29:55.446
(MAN COUGHING)

29:58.079 --> 29:59.080
(DOG YELPING)

29:59.159 --> 30:00.160
(MAN GROANING)

30:00.439 --> 30:01.929
Come meet my friend.

30:03.879 --> 30:05.290
Here she is.

30:05.759 --> 30:06.806
Little Sashenka.

30:07.439 --> 30:09.248
(SASHENKA WHIMPERS)

30:11.399 --> 30:13.447
Did you eat today, master?

30:17.559 --> 30:19.049
Here. (COUGHS)

30:19.199 --> 30:22.043
You have one of these, and don't say
I don't treat you kind 'cause I do.

30:23.199 --> 30:25.008
You'd share it with me?

30:25.079 --> 30:27.002
Yeah, I would. Why not?

30:27.159 --> 30:28.729
And her, too.

30:31.039 --> 30:32.529
Come on. Take.

30:35.799 --> 30:39.246
No, no, no. Not like that.
You won't taste it, master.

30:44.159 --> 30:45.285
Here.

30:45.399 --> 30:46.730
(SASHENKA WHIMPERING)

30:46.799 --> 30:48.528
Little bit of salt.

30:48.879 --> 30:51.120
Now, bit by bit.

30:51.959 --> 30:56.362
And savour it, master. You never know,
this might be the last one you ever see.

31:00.159 --> 31:01.968
Right, a little bit for you, miss.

31:02.079 --> 31:03.683
(SASHENKA WHIMPERING)

31:03.879 --> 31:05.688
Come on, sit up nice.

31:07.519 --> 31:08.759
Sit up nice.

31:09.559 --> 31:10.890
Good girl.

31:11.199 --> 31:12.963
Good girl, Sashenka.

31:13.159 --> 31:14.320
(SIGHS)

31:22.599 --> 31:24.010
Is it good?

31:27.279 --> 31:28.804
It's very good.

31:29.879 --> 31:31.210
Thank you.

31:32.399 --> 31:33.400
Platon Ka ratayev.

31:35.479 --> 31:37.083
Pierre Bezukhov.

31:38.679 --> 31:42.001
HELENE: My dear Pierre,
what is the matter with you?

31:42.759 --> 31:45.239
Why do you not reply to my letters?

31:45.999 --> 31:48.730
I know you would not
wish me to be unhappy, and

31:48.799 --> 31:51.564
what I require from you
is such a little thing.

31:51.719 --> 31:53.403
(SIGHS) The work of a moment.

31:53.479 --> 31:55.686
- (BOTTLES FALLING)
- (GRU NTING)

31:56.159 --> 32:00.323
All I need is a word from you agreeing
that our marriage was never consummated.

32:00.399 --> 32:02.083
This will enable me to marry again.

32:02.839 --> 32:05.683
I know you will do this for me out
of the Christian kindness of your heart.

32:05.759 --> 32:09.480
Dear Pierre, in eternal friendship
and sincere regard,

32:10.079 --> 32:11.080
Helene.

32:13.399 --> 32:17.040
P.S, this matter really is quite urgent.

32:17.159 --> 32:19.127
(SOFT INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC)

32:29.479 --> 32:31.925
NATALYA: Dear Petya says
he's enjoying army life.

32:32.159 --> 32:35.447
And he hopes very much
to see some real fighting soon.

32:35.559 --> 32:38.039
- (SIGHS)
- ILYA: I don't understand, my dear.

32:38.119 --> 32:39.723
It's from Petya.

32:40.479 --> 32:41.844
- Where?
- Oh.

32:43.799 --> 32:45.164
Oh, yes, I see.

32:46.319 --> 32:48.003
SONYA: Someone's coming.

32:48.479 --> 32:52.279
It's Princess Marya.
And the little boy, Prince Andrei's son.

32:53.919 --> 32:55.523
(HORSE NEIGHING)

32:55.799 --> 32:57.039
Come on.

32:58.279 --> 33:01.169
Ah! Ban enfam'.

33:01.679 --> 33:04.080
Oh, this must be his boy.

33:04.559 --> 33:07.927
Princess, you're very
welcome, very welcome...

33:08.159 --> 33:10.241
Forgive me, but he is here.

33:10.319 --> 33:11.730
May I see him?

33:11.799 --> 33:13.608
But of course. Errn...

33:14.319 --> 33:15.445
Why don't you sit down?

33:15.519 --> 33:17.965
No, no, no. If you please,
I'd like to see him straight away.

33:18.039 --> 33:21.168
Sit down, and we'll ring for tea.
There's no hurry, really. No hurry.

33:21.239 --> 33:22.445
(NATALYA CHUCKLES)

33:25.679 --> 33:26.885
(GASPS)

33:27.959 --> 33:30.610
(SEAS)

33:32.599 --> 33:34.806
I'll take you to him. Come.

33:36.839 --> 33:39.410
(FOOTSTEPS ECHOING)

33:39.959 --> 33:40.960
(SIGHS)

33:43.519 --> 33:44.850
How is he?

33:45.199 --> 33:46.564
You'll see.

33:48.399 --> 33:51.243
We were very hopeful,
but there was a...

33:52.399 --> 33:54.720
Change, two days ago.

33:56.199 --> 33:57.564
You'll see.

34:06.159 --> 34:07.843
ANDREI: Oh, Marya.

34:09.518 --> 34:11.521
And Nikolushka, too.

34:11.799 --> 34:13.164
MARYA: How are you now'?

34:13.679 --> 34:15.204
Your health, I mean.

34:16.319 --> 34:19.289
Whereas for that,
you have to ask the doctor.

34:20.438 --> 34:21.440
Thank you for coming.

34:23.679 --> 34:24.679
So...

34:25.079 --> 34:27.047
Here we are, all together.

34:28.478 --> 34:31.244
Isn't it odd, this one
taking care of me?

34:34.279 --> 34:35.405
(SIGHS)

34:35.478 --> 34:36.810
No, Marya.

34:37.839 --> 34:39.364
No crying here.

34:43.079 --> 34:46.367
Let Nikolushka kiss me,
and then take him away.

34:48.518 --> 34:49.520
I'm tired.

34:54.559 --> 34:55.639
Hmm.

34:58.799 --> 35:00.130
So like your mother.

35:01.999 --> 35:03.808
Be happy, Nikolushka.

35:04.359 --> 35:06.600
Hmm? Make me proud of you.

35:08.159 --> 35:09.763
I know you will.

35:12.039 --> 35:13.040
(CLEARS TH ROAT)

35:13.519 --> 35:14.759
Come on.

35:16.479 --> 35:17.890
Wait, Marya.

35:18.079 --> 35:20.525
Let him have your icon
to remember me by.

35:20.599 --> 35:23.250
(VOICE BREAKING)
No, Andrei, don't say that.

35:23.319 --> 35:24.650
Do as I say. Please.

35:31.279 --> 35:32.280
(GROANS)

35:35.119 --> 35:36.609
(ANDREI SIGHS)

35:36.839 --> 35:41.879
(SOFT PIANO MUSIC)

35:44.079 --> 35:47.401
(MARYA SUMS)

35:48.559 --> 35:50.303
Thank you.

35:52.039 --> 35:53.450
(ANDREI EXHALES)

35:54.879 --> 35:56.404
Hey, come on.

36:06.839 --> 36:08.568
(MARYA SOBBING SOFTLY)

36:11.999 --> 36:13.649
Oh, Marya.

36:16.559 --> 36:17.970
MARYA: He's leaving us.

36:18.919 --> 36:20.728
(BOTH CRYING)

36:22.439 --> 36:26.649
(PRAYING IN RUSSIAN)

38:05.239 --> 38:06.923
MARYA: Is it over?

38:09.079 --> 38:10.319
(NATASHA SOBS SOFTLY)

38:29.519 --> 38:30.805
(EXCLAIMS SOFTLY)

38:31.759 --> 38:32.760
He's cold already.

38:36.719 --> 38:38.050
Has he gone?

38:39.279 --> 38:40.883
Where is he now?

38:48.199 --> 38:50.281
So your parents both alive?

38:50.519 --> 38:51.759
PIERRE: Neither of them.

38:51.879 --> 38:53.040
Ah, it's a shame.

38:53.559 --> 38:55.721
Mine's still alive and well.

38:56.439 --> 38:57.600
Any brothers and sisters?

38:57.799 --> 38:58.800
None.

39:00.399 --> 39:03.721
Never mind, I'll be your
brother while we're here.

39:06.519 --> 39:08.681
You know, it was a good job
they took me for the army.

39:09.199 --> 39:12.681
Then my brothers didn't
have to go and leave their families.

39:13.999 --> 39:17.162
Were you taken, or did you
go of your own accord?

39:17.599 --> 39:20.125
I went just to see what it was like.

39:21.599 --> 39:26.002
I used to be a huge admirer of Napoleon,
almost wanted to be him, but...

39:26.839 --> 39:30.764
When I saw what his ambition had done,
so much senseless death,

39:30.839 --> 39:32.921
destruction, I came
to the opposite view,

39:33.319 --> 39:36.607
that the world would be
a better place without him.

39:38.919 --> 39:40.045
I had this idea...

39:41.359 --> 39:43.930
After Borodino,
that I might assassinate Napoleon.

39:43.999 --> 39:46.161
I thought it was my destiny.

39:47.079 --> 39:48.843
(SCOFFS) And look at me now.

39:49.679 --> 39:50.919
You and me.

39:51.519 --> 39:53.647
Too tender-hearted for that game.

39:54.759 --> 39:58.081
I've been in the army 10 years,
never killed anyone.

39:58.599 --> 40:00.044
Or wanted to.

40:01.679 --> 40:04.125
Here, look at little Sashenka.

40:07.079 --> 40:09.923
She could smell your
kind heart right away.

40:10.959 --> 40:12.449
Dogs and cats,

40:12.719 --> 40:13.959
they know more than we do.

40:22.319 --> 40:25.129
(LIGHT WIND BLOWING)

40:28.559 --> 40:30.323
(INHALES) Gentlemen,

40:30.399 --> 40:32.288
with limited supplies
and winter approaching,

40:32.359 --> 40:34.487
our position will deteriorate.

40:34.599 --> 40:38.081
Convey my compliments to all
the regimental commanders.

40:38.959 --> 40:40.961
And instruct them to make ready.

40:41.959 --> 40:43.484
For what, sire?

40:45.599 --> 40:46.839
Retreat.

40:58.119 --> 41:00.599
Come on. Everybody up. Get in line.

41:00.679 --> 41:01.680
What's happening?

41:01.799 --> 41:03.801
Leave, you must go. Get in line.

41:03.879 --> 41:06.280
Why not just let us go free?
Less work for you.

41:06.359 --> 41:08.760
And have you turn up
again and attack us?

41:08.919 --> 41:10.967
No, we are stuck with you.

41:11.319 --> 41:12.400
(MAN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY)

41:12.919 --> 41:15.320
See, master? They're prisoners, too.

41:15.519 --> 41:18.728
SOLDIER: Go, go, come on! Go!

41:27.759 --> 41:30.524
Monsieure capitaine.
Look at this poor fellow.

41:30.799 --> 41:32.449
He can't keep up. (PANTING)

41:32.559 --> 41:33.720
Can't he ride?

41:33.879 --> 41:35.404
He can march or he can die.

41:35.519 --> 41:37.487
All stragglers to be shot. Come on!

41:37.599 --> 41:38.885
On, on!

41:39.079 --> 41:40.159
- Keep up!
- It's all right.

41:42.199 --> 41:43.200
KARATAYE: Look at this.

41:44.879 --> 41:48.042
Oh, Moscow, what have they done to you?

41:48.839 --> 41:52.127
Look at that poor fellow.
They'll leave him like that.

41:54.279 --> 41:56.202
<i>A rré fez!</i> H a <i>Lt!</i>

41:57.679 --> 41:58.965
Prisoners, this way!

41:59.079 --> 42:00.604
SOLDIER: Come on, come on.

42:00.679 --> 42:02.966
(SPEAKING IN FRENCH)

42:08.799 --> 42:12.042
Rambal! Capitaine Rambal!

42:12.559 --> 42:13.560
Mon ami!

42:14.079 --> 42:15.968
PIERRE: Do you remember me, my friend?

42:27.559 --> 42:29.527
Look at that. Thieves.

42:30.559 --> 42:32.402
There's nothing they wouldn't take.

42:32.519 --> 42:34.169
(CROWD WHISTLING AND CH EERING)

42:36.039 --> 42:38.883
Hey, monsieur, leave a few for us.

42:38.959 --> 42:40.768
(WOMEN LAUGHING)

42:44.439 --> 42:45.929
(GRUNTING)

42:46.439 --> 42:47.884
(GROANING)

42:49.119 --> 42:51.326
Prisonniers! A'écoutei!

42:51.439 --> 42:52.565
GUARD: Come on, march!

42:52.719 --> 42:53.925
Alignez-vous!

42:56.239 --> 42:57.764
SOLDIER: Come on.

42:58.279 --> 42:59.724
Alignez-vous!

43:01.079 --> 43:03.889
(SPEAKING FRENCH)

43:04.319 --> 43:05.400
March'!

43:06.519 --> 43:10.968
(MILITARY DRUM PLAYING)

43:16.599 --> 43:18.647
DOCTOR: You must be patient, Contessa.

43:18.759 --> 43:23.048
Two drops a clay, no more, and
nature will work its course. Huh?

43:23.279 --> 43:24.405
I promise you.

43:24.559 --> 43:27.608
Is there really nothing
else you can do for me?

43:27.759 --> 43:30.649
Can't you see I'm desperate?
I can't get married like this.

43:30.919 --> 43:34.048
(SPEAKING ITALIAN)

43:34.119 --> 43:35.245
(IN ENGLISH)
It all will be well.

43:35.319 --> 43:36.366
(PANTING)

43:36.439 --> 43:39.045
We'll come again to see you tomorrow.

43:39.599 --> 43:40.805
Arrivederci.

43:41.159 --> 43:43.207
I have other ladies to attend to now.

43:43.519 --> 43:44.520
(SPEAKING ITALIAN)

43:44.599 --> 43:46.010
Arrivederci.

43:48.079 --> 43:50.810
(WOMEN LAUGHING)

43:52.239 --> 43:56.608
(INDISTINCT SPEAKING)

43:59.879 --> 44:01.643
Ivan.

44:08.559 --> 44:12.200
(GUESTS CHATTERING)

44:14.119 --> 44:16.201
- You know how it is.
- Boris.

44:17.279 --> 44:18.929
Excuse me.

44:22.919 --> 44:24.683
Anna Pavlovna, I'm so sorry I'm late.

44:24.759 --> 44:26.602
You must leave now, Countess.

44:26.879 --> 44:27.880
Really.

44:27.999 --> 44:30.081
You never should have come.

44:30.439 --> 44:32.043
Go, please.

44:33.079 --> 44:34.319
Go, now.

44:42.839 --> 44:43.840
Ha!

44:55.359 --> 44:58.090
(SCREAMING)

44:58.839 --> 45:01.490
(PANTING)

45:08.879 --> 45:12.088
(BREATHING H EAVI LY)

45:25.719 --> 45:27.323
(GROANS)

45:32.719 --> 45:35.450
(GASPING)

46:19.679 --> 46:21.169
It's Borodino.

46:23.039 --> 46:24.404
We're here, brother.

46:24.559 --> 46:25.720
I was.

46:26.639 --> 46:27.879
Were you?

46:28.199 --> 46:29.883
(WIND BLOWING)

46:32.879 --> 46:33.880
(MAN COUGHING)

46:34.159 --> 46:35.365
(SASHENKA WHIMPERING)

46:46.959 --> 46:48.449
(MAN COUGHING)

46:51.399 --> 46:53.367
Oh, she is happy, anyway.

46:56.119 --> 46:57.200
(SASHENKA WHINING)

46:57.279 --> 46:59.805
Warmer down here
out of the... (COUGHING)

47:05.319 --> 47:08.084
- Oh, you go on. I'll catch you up.
- I'll wait.

47:08.839 --> 47:09.840
Go on, go on.

47:10.239 --> 47:11.923
(COUGHING AND CHOKING)

47:14.199 --> 47:15.803
(SOLDIER SPEAKING IN FRENCH)

47:23.439 --> 47:24.440
(sun FIRES)

47:28.359 --> 47:31.169
Get on, or you'll get the same.

47:31.719 --> 47:32.845
Move!

47:34.079 --> 47:35.683
(SASHENKA WHINING)

48:46.079 --> 48:48.366
ANDREI: It would have been
terrible for you, you know?

48:48.959 --> 48:51.610
To have to go on looking after me.

48:51.679 --> 48:53.647
And suffering with me.

48:54.279 --> 48:56.202
I wouldn't have minded.

48:57.319 --> 49:01.608
(SIGHS) To have suffered with you,
that was the best happiness for me.

49:03.199 --> 49:05.725
You didn't have to go then, you see.

49:08.399 --> 49:09.685
(WHISPERS) Love you.

49:12.399 --> 49:15.209
I love you, and now
there's no one for me.

49:18.239 --> 49:20.162
But I will remember you.

49:25.439 --> 49:27.123
But not like this.

49:27.799 --> 49:29.244
Yes.

49:29.959 --> 49:31.882
Yes, like this.

49:33.279 --> 49:34.326
(SIGHS)

49:34.399 --> 49:35.560
But also like...

49:44.599 --> 49:46.601
(SOFILY SOBBING)

49:57.599 --> 49:59.408
(CROWS CAWING)

50:04.359 --> 50:06.202
(SOLDIER SPEAKING IN FRENCH)

50:08.359 --> 50:10.009
(MAN COUGHING)

50:14.919 --> 50:16.250
We could take them now.

50:16.319 --> 50:17.844
Better to wait.

50:18.839 --> 50:21.319
Let them make camp for the night.
We'll take them at dawn.

50:21.399 --> 50:25.085
As you wish.
I like this work. Rich pickings.

50:25.159 --> 50:26.285
Hmm.

50:32.639 --> 50:33.765
Who's this now?

50:37.879 --> 50:40.530
What're you doing out here?
You'll give us all away.

50:40.719 --> 50:42.926
Sorry, sir, I didn't realise.

50:43.999 --> 50:45.000
Uh...

50:45.119 --> 50:47.201
I have this letter for you.

50:47.399 --> 50:50.005
- I'm sorry, it got wet.
- Give it here.

50:56.399 --> 50:57.810
Tell him no.

50:58.799 --> 51:01.405
Colonel Denisov, don't you remember me?

51:02.079 --> 51:03.524
Petya Rostov.

51:04.919 --> 51:05.920
IS it you?

51:06.119 --> 51:08.201
Yes, of course!

51:10.359 --> 51:12.441
- How are you?
- (PETYA EXCLAIMS)

51:13.159 --> 51:15.605
So, you're a real soldier
now, huh? (CHUCKLES)

51:17.639 --> 51:19.880
Well, off with you. And tell your
commander we do it our own way.

51:19.959 --> 51:21.882
But, Denisov, if you please.

51:21.959 --> 51:23.529
Yes, what is it?

51:23.599 --> 51:27.445
I have permission to join your
squad if you give your consent.

51:27.799 --> 51:31.326
- It's rough work for boys, you know.
- I don't mind that, sir.

51:35.279 --> 51:36.610
All right.

51:36.879 --> 51:38.608
We'll try and look after you.

51:39.319 --> 51:42.050
This work, it's not
death and glory stuff.

51:42.119 --> 51:43.530
Not heroics.

51:43.719 --> 51:45.608
We work like the wolves do,
watch and wait,

51:45.679 --> 51:49.047
and pick them off at their weakest
point while they're retreating.

51:49.119 --> 51:51.360
Our job is to see them out of Russia,

51:51.439 --> 51:53.089
and make sure they never return.

51:56.079 --> 51:58.605
None of your crazy
stuff with the boy, now.

51:58.679 --> 52:01.683
We need to send him home
to his mother in one piece.

52:01.759 --> 52:03.727
What do you take me for?

52:04.439 --> 52:06.680
I have a mother, too, you know.

52:10.759 --> 52:12.249
(HORSE SNORTING)

52:15.879 --> 52:17.688
We need to know their strengths,

52:17.759 --> 52:19.329
I'll go down there, scent them out.

52:19.399 --> 52:21.049
Up to you, if you
want to risk your life.

52:21.119 --> 52:22.848
- I'll come with you.
- No, you don't.

52:22.919 --> 52:25.126
Let the boy come.
Come on, son, follow me.

52:25.279 --> 52:26.963
No, come back.

52:28.039 --> 52:29.325
Damn you.

52:32.479 --> 52:35.528
DOLOKHOV: Remember,
speak French or keep your mouth shut.

52:38.759 --> 52:39.760
(SPEAKING FRENCH)

52:50.159 --> 52:52.002
(INDISTINCT SPEAKING)

53:20.519 --> 53:22.442
(SOLDIERS SPEAKING IN FRENCH)

53:45.919 --> 53:48.160
My God, your accent's diabolical!

53:48.239 --> 53:50.241
- Are they coming after us?
- No.

53:50.319 --> 53:51.764
You did well.

53:51.919 --> 53:55.002
Nerves of steel.
We'll make a soldier of you yet.

53:55.079 --> 53:56.604
Thank you, Dolokhov.

53:56.679 --> 53:59.523
And thank you for letting me
come with you.

54:03.399 --> 54:04.400
Good boy.

54:05.119 --> 54:07.360
You'll carry me well tomorrow.

54:07.959 --> 54:09.609
SOLDIER: Still awake, master?

54:09.679 --> 54:10.760
Yes.

54:11.279 --> 54:14.169
Dolokhov and I went down
to the French camp.

54:14.679 --> 54:16.761
You're a brave one, master.

54:17.959 --> 54:19.290
With Dolokhov, it's easy.

54:19.679 --> 54:21.841
He's not afraid of anything.

54:21.919 --> 54:23.205
Not even death itself.

54:23.639 --> 54:25.846
He can handle himself,
that Captain Dolokhov.

54:25.919 --> 54:27.000
Yes.

54:27.719 --> 54:29.244
Yes, he damn well can.

54:31.999 --> 54:34.684
Would you like some raisins? Very good.

54:36.359 --> 54:38.930
- Thank you, master.
- Go on, take the whole bag.

54:38.999 --> 54:40.444
I've got plenty more.

54:40.559 --> 54:41.959
I brought them from home, you know.

54:47.559 --> 54:49.561
Would you sharpen my sabre for me?

54:49.639 --> 54:50.640
It's got blunt.

54:54.199 --> 54:55.564
Actually...

54:57.479 --> 54:59.527
It's never been sharpened.

54:59.599 --> 55:02.364
Give it here, master.
I'll put a good edge on it for you.

55:10.039 --> 55:11.609
(SHARPENING SABRE)

55:31.159 --> 55:32.490
Thank you.

55:36.679 --> 55:37.805
No other breaks.

55:37.879 --> 55:40.610
- Stay in the pack. Follow me, got it?
- Yes, Colonel.

55:40.799 --> 55:42.289
(HORSE NEIGHS)

55:50.479 --> 55:52.129
(IN DISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

56:05.519 --> 56:07.328
(FOOTSTEPS RUMBLING)

56:10.039 --> 56:12.406
ALL: Charge!

56:12.799 --> 56:15.166
(FIRING)

56:19.639 --> 56:20.640
(GRUNTING)

56:22.399 --> 56:24.640
- (GROANING)
- (HORSES NEIGHING)

56:46.519 --> 56:47.520
DENISOV: Petya!

56:54.319 --> 56:55.559
Petya!

56:55.799 --> 56:57.039
(GRUNTING AND GROANING)

56:57.519 --> 56:59.248
(FIRING)

57:02.639 --> 57:03.640
Petya!

57:04.159 --> 57:06.002
No! (EXCLAIMS)

57:11.239 --> 57:13.287
(SCREAMS)

57:19.039 --> 57:20.768
(DENISOV SCREAMING)

57:27.799 --> 57:30.484
(SPEAKING FRENCH)

57:33.159 --> 57:34.843
(SPEAKING FRENCH)

57:39.919 --> 57:41.762
On your knees.

57:44.359 --> 57:46.680
Surrender or die.
It's all the same to me.

57:47.599 --> 57:50.762
Prisoners, poor devils.
Let's have a look at you.

57:51.239 --> 57:52.445
(SIGHS)

57:59.399 --> 58:01.401
PIERRE: Dolokhov. Dolokhov.

58:02.959 --> 58:04.202
Dolokhov.

58:05.199 --> 58:06.439
- Dolokhov.
- Petrushka!

58:06.959 --> 58:08.120
Dolokhov.

58:08.199 --> 58:10.481
Let's get some help here!

58:10.999 --> 58:12.364
(PANTING)

58:14.999 --> 58:16.842
Oh, my friend!

58:19.439 --> 58:23.080
Oh, my friend! (SIGHS)

58:24.879 --> 58:26.324
Thank you.

58:37.359 --> 58:39.168
(NATALYA WAILING)

58:45.239 --> 58:49.164
Oh, why? Oh, why?

58:49.239 --> 58:52.322
Oh, I love you.

59:44.079 --> 59:45.319
(SOLDIER SPEAKING IN FRENCH)

59:45.959 --> 59:46.960
(KNOCK ON DOOR)

59:47.159 --> 59:48.604
- Hmm.
- (DOOR OPENS)

59:49.399 --> 59:50.400
(DOOR CLOSES)

59:51.159 --> 59:53.765
Napoleon has left Russia, Your Grace.

59:59.239 --> 01:00:01.003
We have our victory.

01:00:01.879 --> 01:00:04.086
Nothing left to do.
(SOFT CHUCKLE)

01:00:06.479 --> 01:00:08.447
Russia is saved.

01:00:09.679 --> 01:00:11.363
Thank the Lord.

01:00:21.919 --> 01:00:23.728
I'm so sorry, my love.

01:00:23.799 --> 01:00:26.803
(SHUSHING) Don't cry.

01:00:27.239 --> 01:00:29.446
- (SOBBING)
- (SHUSHING)

01:00:29.999 --> 01:00:33.799
- But I've... I've ruined you all.
- No, no, no.

01:00:33.879 --> 01:00:35.927
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

01:00:36.039 --> 01:00:38.645
(SOFTLY)
Close your eyes. Hmm?

01:00:39.959 --> 01:00:42.007
- You should rest, Mama.
- No.

01:00:42.079 --> 01:00:43.729
I'll stay by him.

01:00:44.279 --> 01:00:46.281
No, he wants me by his side.

01:00:47.359 --> 01:00:48.884
(ILYA SIGHING)

01:00:54.959 --> 01:00:57.690
- NATALYA: There, there.
- (ILYA BREATHING DEEPLY)

01:00:59.639 --> 01:01:02.529
(MAN SINGING IN RUSSIAN)

01:01:21.279 --> 01:01:23.407
(ALL SINGING IN RUSSIAN)

01:01:30.839 --> 01:01:32.170
(SOBBING)

01:01:39.279 --> 01:01:41.043
(SINGING CONTINUES)

01:02:43.359 --> 01:02:45.646
Is... Is anybody there?

01:02:48.799 --> 01:02:50.085
(GRUNTS)

01:02:50.679 --> 01:02:52.124
VALET: Excellency.

01:02:52.359 --> 01:02:54.202
So I'm alive, am I?

01:02:54.639 --> 01:02:56.243
Yes, Excellency.

01:03:00.359 --> 01:03:02.202
How long have I laid here?

01:03:02.359 --> 01:03:04.168
Days, Excellency.

01:03:04.879 --> 01:03:07.200
The doctors said to let you sleep.

01:03:08.119 --> 01:03:11.965
Captain Dolokhov has been here,
and Colonel Denisov.

01:03:12.039 --> 01:03:13.643
I'm hungry...

01:03:14.839 --> 01:03:17.729
Bring my clothes.
Wait, have I got anything to wear?

01:03:17.799 --> 01:03:19.642
Of course, Your Excellency.

01:03:22.639 --> 01:03:24.482
And bring me a barber.

01:03:26.759 --> 01:03:28.887
(FOOTSTEPS RECEDING)

01:03:41.079 --> 01:03:42.763
(EXHALES DEEPLY)

01:03:44.279 --> 01:03:45.724
(INHALES DEEPLY)

01:05:06.519 --> 01:05:08.965
- (PEOPLE SPEAKING IN DISTINCTLY)
- (BABY WAILING)

01:05:24.719 --> 01:05:26.926
MARYA: I'm so sorry
for your loss, Countess.

01:05:26.999 --> 01:05:28.000
(NATALYA SIGHS)

01:05:28.079 --> 01:05:29.490
It must be very hard to bear.

01:05:29.559 --> 01:05:32.324
I've been thinking
about you all so much.

01:05:32.399 --> 01:05:33.639
Oh...

01:05:36.319 --> 01:05:37.525
Princess Bolkonskaya.

01:05:38.919 --> 01:05:40.159
(DOOR OPENING)

01:05:41.119 --> 01:05:42.450
Marya!

01:05:46.999 --> 01:05:49.366
Oh, so you're in Moscow now?

01:05:49.439 --> 01:05:52.363
Yes, with Mademoisell
Bourienne and Nikolushka.

01:05:52.439 --> 01:05:56.046
Oh, we seem like such a little family
in that great gloomy house.

01:05:56.759 --> 01:06:00.161
NATALYA: We take it very kindly
that you came to call on us, Princess.

01:06:00.239 --> 01:06:03.368
We used to have
such a great number of friends.

01:06:03.439 --> 01:06:08.206
But very few have sought us out
in our reduced circumstances.

01:06:08.839 --> 01:06:09.886
Excuse me.

01:06:16.519 --> 01:06:19.329
I wanted to express
my thanks to Count Nikolai.

01:06:19.639 --> 01:06:23.121
I truly believe
he may have saved my life, you know?

01:06:23.559 --> 01:06:25.687
I'll make sure he knows it.

01:06:26.359 --> 01:06:29.841
And I was wondering, perhaps
you could all come and stay with me.

01:06:29.919 --> 01:06:32.923
I've so many rooms and I could ask
your advice about all the improvements

01:06:32.999 --> 01:06:36.208
that need to be made in Moscow
and the Bald Hills.

01:06:37.439 --> 01:06:39.919
MARYA: I hope you don't think
presumptuous of me.

01:06:43.479 --> 01:06:45.129
NIKOLAI: Have you no pride, Mother?

01:06:45.199 --> 01:06:46.803
What's the use of pride, Nikolai?

01:06:47.119 --> 01:06:49.087
Princess Marya is our friend.

01:06:49.559 --> 01:06:52.369
She has a generous heart
and she has the means to help us.

01:06:52.679 --> 01:06:55.125
Think of all the people
our father helped when he was able to.

01:06:55.319 --> 01:06:57.640
NIKOLAI: You may enjoy
the prospect of her charity, Tasha.

01:06:57.719 --> 01:07:00.086
But I, I value
my independence too much, that's all!

01:07:00.439 --> 01:07:04.330
Well, I pray that you come to see things
in a different light.

01:07:04.399 --> 01:07:07.164
In the meantime,
we will accept her generosity,

01:07:07.239 --> 01:07:08.570
and you will pay her a visit!

01:07:09.399 --> 01:07:11.561
Common courtesy demands that!

01:07:20.079 --> 01:07:21.649
SONYA: Is it because of me?

01:07:22.799 --> 01:07:24.085
Is what because of you?

01:07:24.759 --> 01:07:29.287
That you won't tell Princess Bolkonskaya
that you love her and want to marry her.

01:07:30.039 --> 01:07:32.610
No, it's because our family are paupers.

01:07:33.639 --> 01:07:37.121
(SIGHS) Yes, I do feel badly
about you, Sonya. I'd...

01:07:38.319 --> 01:07:40.890
Then please don't.

01:07:44.079 --> 01:07:47.083
I always felt that
we could never be married.

01:07:47.959 --> 01:07:50.007
And she deserves to be happy, Nikolai.

01:07:51.119 --> 01:07:52.450
You're too good.

01:07:53.359 --> 01:07:56.090
How can you be so self-sacrificing?

01:07:57.519 --> 01:08:00.170
Oh, because I'm used to it.

01:08:01.759 --> 01:08:04.524
- NATALYA: Sonya!
- Coming.

01:08:17.879 --> 01:08:19.881
(IN DISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

01:08:27.439 --> 01:08:29.089
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

01:08:36.959 --> 01:08:39.529
My mother sends her compliments,
hopes you're well.

01:08:40.158 --> 01:08:43.447
I'm quite well, thank you,
in the circumstances.

01:08:43.519 --> 01:08:44.759
How is she now?

01:08:44.839 --> 01:08:46.125
She's bearing up, thank you.

01:08:46.679 --> 01:08:50.001
She appreciated your coming to see her.
It was a great comfort to her.

01:09:02.319 --> 01:09:03.559
And you?

01:09:04.238 --> 01:09:05.319
You're well?

01:09:05.839 --> 01:09:07.170
As you see.

01:09:09.319 --> 01:09:11.639
I've had to give up my commission
but that can't be helped.

01:09:11.839 --> 01:09:14.365
Well, you sacrificed yourself for
your family.

01:09:14.839 --> 01:09:18.048
That's so good of you and so sad...

01:09:18.118 --> 01:09:19.689
No, really, there's nothing to praise.

01:09:19.919 --> 01:09:23.560
I blame myself for my reckless conduct
in the past and I deserve to pay for it.

01:09:24.198 --> 01:09:27.328
But now my mother and sister
are to suffer for it, too.

01:09:27.399 --> 01:09:28.810
I'm not worthy of your kindness.

01:09:28.919 --> 01:09:31.206
I thought
you'd let me sympathise with you.

01:09:33.078 --> 01:09:37.720
And we seemed so close
when we were together in Voronezh.

01:09:37.799 --> 01:09:41.645
But now something's gone wrong,
and I don't know why.

01:09:41.719 --> 01:09:45.609
There are a thousand reasons why.
Our family has lost everything.

01:09:46.038 --> 01:09:48.121
The war's over.
I have no profession.

01:09:48.399 --> 01:09:50.207
My poor mother,
who has never wanted for anything,

01:09:50.279 --> 01:09:52.850
now has to darn her own stockings.

01:09:52.919 --> 01:09:55.650
She's so ashamed, she can't even
go out and face her friends.

01:09:56.119 --> 01:09:58.486
My sister's life is over
before it's scarcely begun.

01:09:58.559 --> 01:09:59.970
Then let me help you.

01:10:00.479 --> 01:10:02.481
I've more money
than I know what to do with.

01:10:02.559 --> 01:10:05.039
Don't you see?
How can I ask for your help?

01:10:05.279 --> 01:10:07.486
People will say
that I'm a fortune hunter.

01:10:07.559 --> 01:10:09.960
Nikolai, do you think I care
what people say?

01:10:12.879 --> 01:10:14.005
Now, look.

01:10:15.359 --> 01:10:17.282
You might have changed your mind.

01:10:18.919 --> 01:10:20.125
But if you still feel

01:10:21.079 --> 01:10:23.730
what I think you felt
when we were together in Voronezh...

01:10:24.559 --> 01:10:27.244
I, I still feel what I felt then.

01:10:27.879 --> 01:10:30.280
And if you knew... (CHUCKLES)

01:10:30.359 --> 01:10:33.363
If you knew how long
I've been waiting for you...

01:10:36.239 --> 01:10:37.684
(BOTH CH UCKLING SOFTLY)

01:10:38.719 --> 01:10:40.323
Ma rya, dear Ma rya.

01:10:49.239 --> 01:10:50.923
(MARYA GIGGLING)

01:11:13.639 --> 01:11:15.164
PIERRE: Prince Vassily.

01:11:17.119 --> 01:11:18.484
It's Pierre.

01:11:18.839 --> 01:11:20.000
Pierre Bezukhov.

01:11:20.079 --> 01:11:21.888
Oh, yes. Of course.

01:11:22.799 --> 01:11:24.403
How are you, my boy?

01:11:24.919 --> 01:11:27.399
How are you?
You don't look well.

01:11:28.519 --> 01:11:30.283
She's dead, Pierre.

01:11:31.679 --> 01:11:33.010
MY lovely girl.

01:11:33.279 --> 01:11:34.485
I know.

01:11:35.639 --> 01:11:37.004
Terrible thing.

01:11:37.839 --> 01:11:41.560
It's a terrible thing
to have your children die before you.

01:11:43.159 --> 01:11:46.641
I know I've done
so much wrong in my life.

01:11:46.959 --> 01:11:49.121
But to take them both from me?

01:11:51.239 --> 01:11:53.003
Both my lovely children.

01:11:56.079 --> 01:11:58.320
I've wronged you, too, my friend.

01:11:59.399 --> 01:12:00.639
Can you forgive me?

01:12:03.439 --> 01:12:04.770
Of course.

01:12:05.639 --> 01:12:07.050
Nothing to forgive.

01:12:08.599 --> 01:12:11.409
Come, there's a chilly wind blowing.
Take my arm.

01:12:11.599 --> 01:12:14.250
- Now let me walk you home.
- Thank you.

01:12:31.239 --> 01:12:32.570
Good evening, sir.

01:12:36.479 --> 01:12:40.643
I thought I should call
to congratulate you on your betrothal.

01:12:40.719 --> 01:12:42.960
MARYA: Ooh. Thank you.

01:12:43.039 --> 01:12:45.326
He's the dearest fellow
as I'm sure you know,

01:12:45.399 --> 01:12:47.128
and very lucky to have found you.

01:12:47.199 --> 01:12:48.963
Oh, please don't embarrass me.

01:12:49.479 --> 01:12:52.801
We were so glad to know
that you'd been saved.

01:12:52.919 --> 01:12:55.399
It's the only good news
we'd had in such a long time.

01:12:55.599 --> 01:12:57.488
Yes, Andrei...

01:12:58.439 --> 01:12:59.770
It's a great blow.

01:13:01.159 --> 01:13:04.481
Can you imagine I knew
nothing about him surviving the battle?

01:13:06.679 --> 01:13:09.000
So you were able
to see him before he died?

01:13:09.079 --> 01:13:11.889
Yeah, and he often spoke of you.

01:13:11.959 --> 01:13:14.246
And always very fondly, didn't he?

01:13:17.319 --> 01:13:19.526
- So you found him at the Rostovs?
- (GIGGLES)

01:13:20.359 --> 01:13:22.839
What an odd coincidence.

01:13:24.159 --> 01:13:26.446
Was she with him at the end?

01:13:27.679 --> 01:13:29.522
Pierre, don't you see who's here?

01:13:32.839 --> 01:13:34.000
Natasha?

01:13:36.919 --> 01:13:38.603
Have I changed so very much?

01:13:41.399 --> 01:13:43.686
No. No.

01:13:44.999 --> 01:13:47.764
No, I didn't see you.
I didn't expect to see you. I...

01:13:48.159 --> 01:13:49.763
I never thought I'd...

01:13:49.919 --> 01:13:51.523
Very happy to see you, Pierre.

01:13:51.639 --> 01:13:53.368
Yes, oh, of course...

01:13:54.759 --> 01:13:56.045
Likewise.

01:13:59.039 --> 01:14:00.882
So you didn't know of Helene's death?

01:14:02.279 --> 01:14:03.485
No.

01:14:03.919 --> 01:14:05.842
You know, she wrote to me
asking to see me,

01:14:05.919 --> 01:14:08.047
but I, I never received her letter.

01:14:09.439 --> 01:14:11.407
We weren't on good terms.

01:14:11.479 --> 01:14:14.847
But such a death without friends,
without consolation,

01:14:14.919 --> 01:14:16.444
I feel so sorry for her.

01:14:18.119 --> 01:14:20.247
Oh, so you're a bachelor
and eligible again.

01:14:22.119 --> 01:14:24.087
Yes, I suppose I am.

01:14:26.799 --> 01:14:30.406
He was such an extraordinary little man.
He was just a peasant.

01:14:30.479 --> 01:14:33.926
You know, but he seemed to
have grasped the secret of how to live.

01:14:35.439 --> 01:14:36.850
He never worried.

01:14:36.919 --> 01:14:41.402
He took pleasure in the good things,
and endured the bad things cheerfully.

01:14:41.479 --> 01:14:43.243
And his little dog.

01:14:43.599 --> 01:14:45.044
How he loved her.

01:14:46.239 --> 01:14:48.401
"She knows how to ask for love," he'd say,

01:14:48.479 --> 01:14:49.765
"and she knows how to give it."

01:14:49.839 --> 01:14:51.170
What else can you ask?

01:14:51.999 --> 01:14:54.320
And he was right, I think.

01:14:55.359 --> 01:14:58.090
So now I'm trying to live like him,
is that ridiculous?

01:14:58.159 --> 01:15:00.446
No. No, it's not ridiculous at all.

01:15:01.319 --> 01:15:03.560
Tell us more about him,
tell us all about him.

01:15:05.039 --> 01:15:07.565
I should go.
I've kept you up far too late.

01:15:07.639 --> 01:15:10.927
But might I call again? Soon?

01:15:10.999 --> 01:15:13.240
Of course, you'll always be welcome.

01:15:18.039 --> 01:15:20.246
NATASHA: Oh, he's such a dear friend.

01:15:20.359 --> 01:15:22.407
But now it's as if...

01:15:23.159 --> 01:15:24.968
I don't know what it is, it's...

01:15:25.759 --> 01:15:28.922
It's as if he's fresh
from the bathhouse, all pure and clean.

01:15:29.439 --> 01:15:31.646
Notjust on the outside,
but on the inside, too.

01:15:31.719 --> 01:15:34.404
Well, I knew he had a true heart
the first time I met him.

01:15:35.399 --> 01:15:36.924
(BOTH SIGHING)

01:15:43.039 --> 01:15:44.609
(SIGHING DEEPLY)

01:16:42.399 --> 01:16:44.447
Princess, help me.
I haven't slept a wink.

01:16:44.519 --> 01:16:45.930
What am Ito do?
Has she said anything?

01:16:45.999 --> 01:16:47.444
May I hope?

01:16:47.519 --> 01:16:49.408
I know I'm not worthy of her, but...

01:16:50.399 --> 01:16:51.844
I've loved her so long.

01:16:53.159 --> 01:16:55.765
Tell me what to do and I will do it.

01:16:56.839 --> 01:16:58.921
Well, I think
you should ask her yourself.

01:17:00.199 --> 01:17:01.849
I'll go and fetch her.

01:17:16.959 --> 01:17:18.643
(CLEARING TH ROAT)

01:17:35.039 --> 01:17:36.484
Dearest Natasha.

01:17:38.199 --> 01:17:40.566
I know I've been a clown
and wasted my life,

01:17:40.639 --> 01:17:42.209
but I have to ask you.

01:17:42.319 --> 01:17:46.529
Say no, and I'll go to Petersburg,
and never bother you again.

01:17:48.239 --> 01:17:49.445
But...

01:17:53.599 --> 01:17:55.488
Do you think you could love me?

01:17:59.959 --> 01:18:02.121
Yes. Yes, I could.

01:18:04.239 --> 01:18:05.684
Yes, I do.

01:18:06.159 --> 01:18:07.604
Do you, Pierre?

01:18:35.679 --> 01:18:37.249
(CHILDREN LAUGHING)

01:18:41.999 --> 01:18:44.366
(PEOPLE SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY)

01:18:49.839 --> 01:18:53.127
NATASHA: Oh, Nikolushka!
How tall you've grown!

01:18:53.679 --> 01:18:55.488
I think you're going
to be taller than your father.

01:18:55.559 --> 01:18:58.369
I hope not. I'd like to be exactly
the same height as he was.

01:18:58.439 --> 01:19:00.965
- Oh, wow! Really?
- (CHILD LAUGHING)

01:19:01.279 --> 01:19:03.043
Oh, is she fast asleep?

01:19:05.479 --> 01:19:07.607
(IN DISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

01:19:11.319 --> 01:19:12.889
Where's Pierre?

01:19:13.599 --> 01:19:15.010
NIKOLUSHKA: Here he comes.

01:19:21.319 --> 01:19:22.650
Pierre!

01:19:22.719 --> 01:19:24.801
Will you read this,
so we can argue about it?

01:19:24.959 --> 01:19:26.165
Will do.

01:19:26.719 --> 01:19:30.280
Ooh! Hey, do I get a kiss
on your nameday?

01:19:31.439 --> 01:19:33.919
PIERRE: They say
sufferings are misfortunes.

01:19:35.079 --> 01:19:36.205
But if I was asked,

01:19:36.279 --> 01:19:38.930
would I stay as I was
before I was taken prisoner?

01:19:38.999 --> 01:19:40.763
Or go through it all again?

01:19:42.799 --> 01:19:45.962
I would say, "For God's sake,
let me be a prisoner again."

01:19:49.159 --> 01:19:53.642
Come, let's sit and eat, and give
thanks for our good fortune.

01:19:53.759 --> 01:19:55.761
- (BABY COOING)
- For me?

01:19:55.839 --> 01:19:57.728
PIERRE: When our lives
are knocked off course,

01:19:57.799 --> 01:19:59.961
we imagine everything in them is lost.

01:20:02.959 --> 01:20:06.680
But it is only the start of
something new and good.

01:20:19.679 --> 01:20:23.161
As long as there is life,
there is happiness.

01:20:25.879 --> 01:20:27.529
There is a great deal.

01:20:27.599 --> 01:20:29.567
A great deal still to come.

